s just on Java tests. I’m also thinking about what resource bundles are included in native support. The JDK likely has localized bundles like \\\"sun.util.resources.LocaleNames,\\\" which may be usable, but I’ll need to check.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating ResourceBundle behavior**\\n\\nI'm looking into whether ResourceBundleHandler's public getBundle can accept an arbitrary base name, even though the source suggests using a fully qualified class name. It seems that using JDK resources might be fine, but I want to focus on testing the behavior of the HSQLDB class rather than the resource itself. I could check if the bundle is not null, possibly with \\\"US.\\\" However, modules might not export, even though ResourceBundle can load non-exported resources. I wonder if I could use \\\"sun.util.resources.CurrencyNames\\\" or \\\"sun.util.resources.LocaleNames.\\\" I'll need to check JDK files in case JAVA_HOME is set to version 25.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_z5RDdlreTo6F7Jim5fd1SplJ|fc_0f25f6128600ab5a016a1185a6459081938d5575971919849b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "echo $JAVA_HOME && find \"$JAVA_HOME\" -path '*jmods/java.base.jmod' -print -quit"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1225, "output": 1401, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29250, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779533197499, "responseId": "resp_0f25f6128600ab5a016a11858e20b48193b5819cb4c9aae897"}}
